cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with the task of diagnosing thorax diseases on chest radiography using deep learning-based computer vision techniques. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network with an attention mechanism for effective diagnosis of thorax diseases, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based solution for diagnosing thorax diseases on chest radiography using deep learning techniques. 
4. cs.MED (Medical Imaging) - The paper deals with the task of diagnosing thorax diseases on chest radiography, which is a sub-domain of medical imaging. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper proposes a model that can adaptively focus on pathologically abnormal regions in chest radiography, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
